<subSubSection id="B9A0650BFFD9F554FF715F106097FE42" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="158" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="F1053680FFD9F554FF715F1067F0FED6" blockId="6.[151,1436,1845,2016]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,153,323]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="158" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
Type data: In the original description 
<bibRefCitation id="952B4B71FFD9F555FDA55F1366E6F8BD" author="Perez, J." box="[579,724,1881,1908]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" pagination="39 - 41" refId="ref19705" refString="Perez, J. (1905) Hymenopteres nouveaux du Mexique. Bulletin, Museum d'Historie Naturalle, Paris, 11, 39 - 41." type="journal article" year="1905">Pérez (1905)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that the provenance of the type specimen(s) was uncertain, citing the type locality as “ 
<collectingCountry id="89AD7610FFD9F555FD855F3766E2F85E" box="[611,720,1917,1943]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Mexique</collectingCountry>
?”. 
<bibRefCitation id="952B4B71FFD9F555FD095F3767AFF85E" author="Snelling, R. R." box="[751,925,1917,1943]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref20589" refString="Snelling, R. R. (1984) Studies on the taxonomy and distribution of American Centridine bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History, 347, 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1984">Snelling (1984)</bibRefCitation>
indicated he studied the “type” of 
<taxonomicName id="36BA4D03FFD9F555FAFB5F3461A4F851" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1905" box="[1309,1430,1918,1944]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confinis">
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFD9F555FAFB5F346102F851" box="[1309,1328,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFD9F555FADB5F3461A4F851" box="[1341,1430,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">confinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, assuming that it was the 
<typeStatus id="2E018822FFD9F555FE165FEB6660F872" box="[496,594,1953,1979]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">holotype</typeStatus>
of the species. Due to the lack of evidence on the number of specimens used by 
<bibRefCitation id="952B4B71FFD9F555FEE05F8F65A4F829" author="Perez, J." box="[262,406,1989,2016]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" pagination="39 - 41" refId="ref19705" refString="Perez, J. (1905) Hymenopteres nouveaux du Mexique. Bulletin, Museum d'Historie Naturalle, Paris, 11, 39 - 41." type="journal article" year="1905">Pérez (1905)</bibRefCitation>
to describe that species, according to the 
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFD9F555FC8A5F8F679FF816" box="[876,941,1989,2015]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">ICZN</collectionCode>
Article number 74.6 the Snelling’s assump- tion can be treated as a valid 
<typeStatus id="2E018822FFD8F554FDC858D366A7FF7A" box="[558,661,153,179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation. During this research, a female was found in the 
<collectionCode id="97ABAE45FFD8F554FAAA58D361AEFF7A" box="[1356,1436,153,179]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">MNHP</collectionCode>
without a locality label, bearing only two labels indicating its type status. If 
<bibRefCitation id="952B4B71FFD8F554FB8058F76119FF1E" author="Snelling, R. R." box="[1126,1323,189,215]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref20589" refString="Snelling, R. R. (1984) Studies on the taxonomy and distribution of American Centridine bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History, 347, 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1984">Snelling’s (1984)</bibRefCitation>
<typeStatus id="2E018822FFD8F554FAD058F761AFFF1E" box="[1334,1437,189,215]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation is valid (i.e. it actually belongs to the type series of 
<taxonomicName id="36BA4D03FFD8F554FC4D58AB6016FF32" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1905" box="[939,1060,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confinis">
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFD8F554FC4D58AB678CFF32" box="[939,958,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFD8F554FC2D58AB6016FF32" box="[971,1060,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">confinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) then the synonymy between this species and 
<taxonomicName id="36BA4D03FFD8F554FE8C594F65FEFED6" box="[362,460,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFD8F554FE8C594F654FFED6" box="[362,381,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C3CEEA92FFD8F554FE6D594F65FEFED6" box="[395,460,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proposed by him (
<bibRefCitation id="952B4B71FFD8F554FD78594F6776FED6" author="Snelling, R. R." box="[670,836,261,287]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref20589" refString="Snelling, R. R. (1984) Studies on the taxonomy and distribution of American Centridine bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History, 347, 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1984">Snelling, 1984</bibRefCitation>
) is correct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1053680FFD8F554FF71596365F0FE8A" blockId="7.[151,1437,153,323]" box="[151,450,297,323]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
